---Question
A differential equation is
---Type
onechoice
---Answers
~\( An equation that uses differences to evaluate derivatives. \)
~\( An equation that has derivatives in it dealing with many factors. \)
~\( An equation that uses differentials to approximate an area. \)
=\( An equation relating an unknown function and one or more of its derivatives. \)
---Comment
Check the notes!

---Question

Consider the equation dy/dt = ky. What function satisfies this equation?
---Type
onechoice
---Answers
~\( y = e^t \)
~\( y = ke^{kt} \)
=\( y = Ae^{kt} \)
~\( y = Ae^{t} \)
---Comment

---Question
Given dy/dt - 1/y + 2 = 0, y(1) = 1, describe the long term behaviour of this differential equation.
---Type
onechoice
---Answers
=\( This function rapidly descends to 0.5 and stays there. \)
~\( This function rapidly ascends to 0.5 and stays there.  \)
~\(This function rapidly descends to 0.5 and then oscillates between -1 and 1. \)
~\(This function rapidly descends to 1 and stays there. \)
---Comment

